26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fdp%252FB0073LGECW%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESee%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fec30-laundry-detergent-review%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777263858000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F624b3cb2e22adb0018d1f4f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fec30-laundry-detergent-review%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20EC30%20Laundry%20Detergent%20is%20a%20water-free%20swatch%20that%20cleans%20your%20clothes%20without%20plastic%20packaging%20and%20takes%20up%20far%20less%20room%20than%20a%20jug%20of%20soap.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20get%20bloodstains%20out%20of%20your%20sheets%2C%20period.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Light%20purple%20sheets%20on%20a%20bed%20with%20small%20bloodstains%20on%20them.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62912f96ff955c0019c5d696%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBloodstains%20happen%3B%20fortunately%2C%20they're%20usually%20removeable.%3Cp%3EArman%20Zhenikeyev%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBloodstains%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20remove%2C%20especially%20when%20dried.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUse%20cold%20water%20on%20a%20bloodstain%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20gently%20dabbing%20at%20the%20stain%20without%20rubbing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHydrogen%20peroxide%20and%20oxygen%20or%20enzyme%20cleaners%20can%20help%20remove%20bloodstains.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBloodstains%20happen%2C%20including%20on%20bedsheets.%20They%20are%20notoriously%20difficult%20to%20remove%2C%20especially%20once%20they're%20dry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20options%20to%20try.%20The%20most%20important%20things%20to%20remember%20are%20to%20act%20quickly%20and%20never%20use%20hot%20water%20or%20heat%20on%20a%20bloodstain.%20Products%20like%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20and%20oxygen%20and%20enzyme%20cleaners%20can%20help%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'll%20help%20you%20get%20rid%20of%20bloodstains%2C%20old%20and%20new%2C%20whether%20they're%20from%20a%20nosebleed%20or%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3e9f77f-024e-4dae-a8a6-d4e5db82f408%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20get%20bloodstains%20out%20of%20sheets%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20you'll%20need%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECold%20water%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20clean%20cloth%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHydrogen%20peroxide%20(check%20for%20color-safeness%20first)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20enzyme%20cleaner%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20oxygen%20cleaner%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fdc34569-2258-4ef2-8645-974365cac837%5C%22%3EUse%20cold%20water%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20this%20depends%20on%20how%20fresh%20the%20bloodstains%20are%20on%20your%20sheets%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jessica%20Samson%2C%20cleaning%20expert%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.maids.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Maids%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20fresh%20stains%2C%20use%20cold%20water%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20act%20quickly%2C%20the%20water%20may%20get%20most%20of%20the%20blood%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Corinna%20and%20Theresa%20Williams%2C%20co-founders%20of%20the%20eco-friendly%20laundromat%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcelsious.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECelsious%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20an%20email.%20Saturating%20the%20stain%20may%20cause%20it%20to%20spread%2C%20so%20first%20try%20dabbing%20with%20a%20cloth%20before%20rinsing%20in%20the%20sink.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENever%20wash%20a%20bloodstain%20with%20hot%20water.%20The%20heat%20causes%20the%20stain%20to%20set%2C%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20remove.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227ef5004-6756-4f93-a975-f067be041f8f%5C%22%3ETry%20hydrogen%20peroxide%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20stain%20persists%2C%20you'll%20need%20some%20extra%20supplies.%20For%20white%20sheets%2C%20you%20can%20try%20hydrogen%20peroxide.%20%26quot%3BCover%20the%20stained%20area%20with%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20and%20blot%20with%20a%20clean%20towel%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Williams%20sisters%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20test%20an%20inconspicuous%20part%20of%20the%20fabric%20to%20see%20if%20the%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20bleaches%20dyed%20or%20patterned%20sheets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22924e1b3a-04c8-4f7e-8280-04f04f602d38%5C%22%3ETry%20an%20oxygen%20cleaner%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20worried%20about%20using%20peroxide%20on%20colorful%20sheets%2C%20the%20Williamses%20suggest%20an%20oxygen%20cleaner.%20You%20can%20spot-treat%20smaller%20stains%20or%20soak%20sheets%20with%20larger%20or%20older%20stains%20overnight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20powdered%20oxygen%20cleaners%20may%20need%20warm%20or%20hot%20water%20to%20activate%2C%20so%20you'll%20want%20to%20add%20cold%20water%20to%20the%20resulting%20mixture%20before%20applying%20it%20to%20the%20stain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269e3a5bf-e93f-4e82-a076-282da34a408a%5C%22%3ETry%20an%20enzyme%20cleaner%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEnzyme%20cleaners%2C%20like%20those%20used%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-pet-vacuum%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epet%20stains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20can%20also%20be%20effective%20in%20cleaning%20bloodstains.%20Be%20sure%20to%20read%20the%20label%2C%20as%20they're%20not%20safe%20for%20all%20fabrics%2C%20like%20silk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEnzyme%20cleaners%20shouldn't%20be%20used%20on%20wool%20or%20silk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22370b517a-8ba6-4423-adce-0572c3ad9ee4%5C%22%3EBleach%20works%20for%20white%20sheets%20but%20has%20drawbacks%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBleach%20is%20a%20cleaning%20staple%20for%20many%20because%20it%20works%20well%20for%20bloodstains%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdoes-bleach-kill-germs-and-viruses%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekills%20germs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20it%20can%20be%20harsh%20on%20fabric%20and%20lead%20to%20discoloration%20if%20you%20use%20too%20much.%20Also%2C%20it%20will%20ruin%20colorful%20fabric.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c5e1a94-b427-45b1-a94b-3d33a88cd623%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20get%20blood%20out%20of%20sheets%20without%20washing%20them%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221883%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pair%20of%20hands%20holding%20a%20shirt's%20laundry%20care%20label%20so%20they%20can%20read%20it%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a942790ed48c0019e57483%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221412%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlways%20check%20the%20washing%20instructions%20on%20your%20sheets%20before%20introducing%20new%20cleaning%20methods.%3Cp%3Eartursfoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBloodstains%20can%20be%20stubborn%2C%20so%20it's%20best%20to%20pretreat%20them%20before%20putting%20your%20sheets%20in%20the%20washer.%20Use%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20(for%20white%20sheets)%2C%20oxygen%20cleaners%2C%20or%20enzyme%20cleaners%2C%20and%20cold%20water%20to%20either%20spot-treat%20or%20soak%20the%20sheet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20stain%20persists%2C%20repeat%20the%20process%20until%20the%20stain%20is%20removed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Samson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c2cb1c6-b1e7-441f-95c3-92b57db8175a%5C%22%3ECan%20you%20remove%20bloodstains%20with%20baking%20soda%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20glass%20jar%20of%20baking%20soda%20next%20to%20a%20bottle%20of%20laundry%20detergent%20on%20top%20of%20a%20pile%20of%20clothes%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a941cf5d47cc0018e91cca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBaking%20soda%20isn't%20the%20most%20effective%20cleaner%20for%20bloodstains.%3Cp%3EThamKC%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20baking%20soda%20(sodium%20bicarbonate)%20can%20remove%20odors%20and%20some%20stains%2C%20it's%20not%20as%20effective%20for%20blood%20as%20an%20oxygen%20cleaner%20with%20sodium%20percarbonate%2C%20said%20the%20Williams%20sisters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSodium%20percarbonate%20works%20by%20releasing%20oxygen%20once%20it's%20exposed%20to%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20release%20of%20oxygen%20lifts%20stains%20and%20dirt%20off%20whatever%20you're%20cleaning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1e19385-ed85-4b68-8608-067797b438f5%5C%22%3EFour%20things%20you%20should%20never%20do%20to%20remove%20bloodstains%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4dfeda6-0d8f-4267-8118-a841e75e3ae6%5C%22%3ENever%20use%20hot%20water%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHot%20water%20sets%20the%20bloodstain%20and%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20remove%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Samson.%20While%20hot%20water%20works%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20stains%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20much%20more%20difficult%20to%20remove%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227fa67ee7-da7a-4f8e-a340-e455f6704a77%5C%22%3EDon't%20leave%20a%20bloodstain%20to%20dry%20if%20possible%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20ignore%20your%20bloodstain%20and%20let%20it%20set%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20Williamses.%20The%20faster%20you%20can%20treat%20it%20with%20cold%20water%2C%20the%20easier%20it%20will%20be%20to%20remove.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20stain%2C%20let%20the%20sheets%20sit%20in%20cold%20water%20with%20some%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20(if%20it%20won't%20bleach%20the%20fabric)%2C%20oxygen%20cleaner%2C%20or%20enzyme%20cleaner.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c58870c1-c7d6-43d6-bcb6-77ab5727832e%5C%22%3ENever%20rub%20a%20fresh%20bloodstain%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20want%20to%20be%20gentle%20as%20you're%20cleaning%20a%20fresh%20stain.%20Rubbing%20it%20could%20push%20the%20stain%20further%20into%20the%20fabric.%20Start%20by%20blotting%2C%20then%20run%20it%20under%20cold%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20stains%20may%20require%20more%20elbow%20grease%2C%20but%20you%20should%20try%20soaking%20them%20several%20times%20instead%20of%20vigorously%20rubbing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238f6930a-37e3-4034-aaf4-14a87210d55d%5C%22%3EDon't%20dry%20your%20sheets%20until%20you're%20sure%20they're%20clean%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20hot%20water%2C%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20the%20dryer's%20heat%20if%20there's%20still%20blood%20on%20your%20sheets.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20blood%20doesn't%20come%20out%20in%20the%20wash%20and%20goes%20into%20the%20dryer%2C%20that's%20likely%20going%20to%20set%20your%20stain%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20Williams%20sisters.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20have%20a%20really%20hard%20time%20getting%20rid%20of%20it%20after%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bcbb9090-2eb4-4f01-9e8e-8f97b8a6f84b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsider's%20takeaway%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20is%20of%20the%20essence%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20bloodstains.%20You'll%20want%20to%20immediately%20blot%20the%20sheet%20then%20rinse%20with%20cold%20water%20to%20remove%20as%20much%20of%20the%20stain%20as%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20dried%20blood%20or%20stubborn%20stains%2C%20you%20can%20use%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20(though%20you'll%20want%20to%20test%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20doesn't%20bleach)%20or%20oxygen%20or%20enzyme%20cleaners.%20You%20may%20need%20to%20repeatedly%20soak%20your%20sheets%20for%20long%20periods%20of%20time%20to%20fully%20remove%20the%20bloodstain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%20that%20heat%20will%20set%20the%20stain%2C%20so%20don't%20use%20hot%20water%20or%20put%20the%20sheet%20in%20the%20dryer%20until%20you've%20fully%20removed%20the%20blood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-get-blood-out-of-sheets%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777263800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6291328df099c4001956ba05%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-get-blood-out-of-sheets%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bloodstains%20are%20notoriously%20difficult%20to%20clean%2C%20but%20we%20asked%20experts%20how%20to%20rid%20your%20sheets%20of%20the%20tricky%20mess.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putting%20your%20comforter%20into%20a%20duvet%20cover%20is%20simple%20%E2%80%94%20here's%20how%20to%20do%20it%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Someone%20laying%20in%20a%20bed%20under%20a%20Brooklinen%20Duvet%20Cover.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd2ce84ef9f30019f88fed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDuvet%20covers%20are%20essentially%20sheets%20that%20encase%20and%20protect%20comforters%20and%20duvets.%3Cp%3EBrooklinen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20address%20the%20elephants%20in%20the%20room%20first.%20A%20duvet%20is%20a%20plain%20down-filled%20blanket%20without%20any%20decorative%20designs%20or%20a%20cover%20%E2%80%94%20think%20of%20it%20as%20a%20basic%20pillow.%20A%20comforter%20is%20a%20flatter%20version%20of%20a%20duvet%2C%20sometimes%20with%20a%20quilted%20sewing%20pattern.%20Many%20people%20use%20the%20two%20terms%20interchangeably%2C%20same%20with%20many%20companies%20who%20design%20them.%20Both%20go%20over%20your%20bedsheets%20like%20any%20other%20blanket%20and%20both%20need%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-duvet-cover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20duvet%20covers%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20say%20%26quot%3Bneed%26quot%3B%20with%20conviction%20because%20the%20advantages%20of%20duvet%20covers%20are%20twofold%3A%20You%20can%20wash%20them%20more%20easily%20and%20frequently%20than%20bulky%20comforters%20or%20duvets%2C%20and%20you%20can%20swap%20them%20out%20regularly%20to%20give%20your%20bedding%20a%20fresh%20look%20with%20new%20colors%20and%20patterns.%20The%20more%20covers%20you%20own%2C%20the%20more%20variety%20of%20styles%20you%20can%20have%20%E2%80%94%20just%20like%20with%20sheets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInsider%20Reviews%20has%20personally%20tested%20a%20number%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-comforter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20comforters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20first%20problem%20we%20all%20encounter%20is%20how%20to%20even%20get%20the%20duvet%20cover%20on.%20This%20frustration%20is%20enough%20to%20drive%20many%20people%20away%2C%20but%20we've%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20research%20and%20tried%20several%20different%20methods%20to%20find%20the%20easiest%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20put%20on%20a%20duvet%20cover%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETurn%20your%20duvet%20cover%20inside%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESpread%20it%20across%20your%20mattress%20with%20its%20opening%20at%20the%20foot%20of%20the%20bed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELay%20your%20duvet%20on%20top%20of%20the%20cover.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20your%20duvet%20and%20duvet%20cover%20have%20inner%20ties%2C%20fasten%20them%20now.%20If%20not%2C%20you%20can%20use%20large%20safety%20pins%20to%20fasten%20the%20corners%20of%20the%20cover%20to%20the%20duvet%2C%20or%20simply%20do%20without.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStarting%20from%20the%20head%20of%20your%20bed%2C%20roll%20the%20duvet%20and%20its%20cover%20together%20like%20a%20burrito.%20It's%20easiest%20if%20you%20have%20a%20partner%2C%20but%20if%20not%2C%20switch%20from%20side%20to%20side%20as%20you%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20your%20%26quot%3Bburrito%26quot%3B%20is%20rolled%2C%20fold%20the%20duvet%20cover%20opening%20around%20the%20bedding%20bundle.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EClose%20your%20duvet%20cover%20with%20its%20zipper%2C%20buttons%2C%20or%20ties.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUnroll%20your%20%26quot%3Bburrito%26quot%3B%20towards%20the%20top%20of%20the%20bed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFluff%20as%20necessary%2C%20and%20voila!%20Your%20duvet%20is%20in%20its%20cover.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-put-on-a-duvet-cover%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777263747000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd2dd2bd8c0900184e8e1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-put-on-a-duvet-cover%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Putting%20a%20duvet%20on%20is%20a%20lot%20easier%20than%20it%20looks.%20Here's%20how%20to%20put%20a%20duvet%20cover%20on%20a%20comforter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mgokey30%40gmail.com%20(Malarie%20Gokey%2CMichelle%20Ullman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20dry%20clean%20clothes%20at%20home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22laundry%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e94748cc02320586a5d94e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDry%20cleaning%20is%20often%20recommended%20for%20suits%2C%20wool%20coats%2C%20and%20thick%20knits%2C%20and%20for%20fabrics%20like%20silk%2C%20wool%2C%20cashmere%2C%20and%20even%20raw%20denim.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20dry%20cleaning%20can%20take%20a%20big%20bite%20out%20of%20your%20budget%20and%20time.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20are%20the%20best%20at-home%20dry%20cleaning%20tips%20and%20products%20so%20you%20can%20save%20some%20money%20and%20protect%20your%20clothes.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-use-a-portable-washing-machine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEverything%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20buying%20and%20using%20a%20portable%20washing%20machine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnless%20you're%20lucky%20enough%20to%20have%20a%20local%20dry%20cleaner%20that%20readily%20offers%20pick-up%20and%20delivery%20with%20just%20a%20quick%20phone%20call%2C%20there%20may%20come%20a%20time%20when%20you%20need%20to%20clean%20a%20dry-clean-only%20garment%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20time%20for%20me%20was%20when%20I%20discovered%20my%20then-high%20school%20senior%20son's%20rumpled%20and%20soiled%20suit%20late%20at%20night%2C%20only%20to%20find%20that%20he%20needed%20it%20the%20next%20morning%20for%20a%20scholarship%20interview.%20Thankfully%2C%20I%20had%20a%20dry%20cleaning%20kit%20on%20the%20laundry%20room%20shelf%20so%20a%20crisis%20was%20averted.%20I%20spot-cleaned%20stains%20with%20the%20kit%2C%20gave%20it%20a%20tumble%20in%20the%20dryer%20and%20a%20good%20press%20with%20an%20iron%2C%20and%20the%20suit%20was%20presentable%20for%20the%20next%20day.%20And%20he%20got%20the%20scholarship%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhy%20you%20should%20dry%20clean%20clothes%20at%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22laundry%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e948e41dcd88c6b2f186936%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EEmily%20May%2Fflickr%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20many%20hours%20in%20university%20labs%20learning%20how%20different%20fibers%20and%20fabrics%20react%20to%20cleaning%20methods%20and%20solutions.%20And%20while%20detergents%20and%20washers%20have%20evolved%2C%20some%20fabrics%20just%20don't%20hold%20up%20well%20when%20exposed%20to%20water%20for%20long%20periods.%20So%20to%20save%20money%2C%20I%20began%20using%20different%20brands%20of%20at-home%20dry%20cleaning%20kits%20when%20they%20first%20hit%20the%20market%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWill%20an%20at-home%20dry%20cleaner%20eliminate%20your%20need%20for%20professional%20dry%20cleaning%3F%20No.%20Will%20an%20at-home%20dry%20cleaner%20help%20you%20remove%20small%20stains%2C%20freshen%2C%20and%20remove%20wrinkles%20so%20you%20can%20get%20another%20wear%20out%20of%20your%20clothes%20before%20a%20more%20thorough%20professional%20cleaning%3F%20Yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20at%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20at-home%20dry%20cleaning%2C%20you'll%20quickly%20see%20why%20keeping%20a%20kit%20on%20hand%20is%20valuable%20for%20more%20than%20last-minute%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAt-home%20cleaning%20is%20less%20expensive%20than%20professional%20dry%20cleaning%20and%20can%20cost%20as%20little%20as%2050%20cents%20per%20garment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20kits%20are%20safe%20for%20most%20fabrics%2C%20convenient%20and%20take%20only%20around%2015-20%20minutes%20to%20use.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20kits%20can%20remove%20small%20stains%2C%20freshen%20fabrics%20by%20helping%20to%20remove%20smoke%20and%20body%20odors%2C%20and%20help%20you%20get%20another%20wear%20from%20a%20garment%20before%20taking%20it%20to%20a%20professional%20cleaner.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAt-home%20dry%20cleaning%20creates%20a%20smaller%20environmental%20impact%20since%20the%20cleaning%20chemicals%20are%20less%20caustic%2C%20you%20have%20less%20waste%20from%20protective%20plastic%20bags%20and%20extra%20hangers%2C%20and%20no%20time%20is%20spent%20on%20the%20road%20to%20pick%20up%20and%20deliver%20clothes.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20downside%20is%20that-home%20dry%20cleaners%20don't%20thoroughly%20saturate%20fabrics%20like%20the%20solutions%20at%20your%20professional%20cleaner%2C%20so%20they%20aren't%20great%20at%20removing%20large%20areas%20of%20heavy%20soil%2C%20especially%20grease%20and%20body%20oils.%20And%20while%20the%20kits%20are%20perfect%20for%20freshening%20knit%20sweaters%2C%20jeans%2C%20and%20unstructured%20shirts%20and%20blouses%2C%20tailored%20clothes%20like%20suit%20jackets%20and%20pleated%20skirts%20won't%20come%20out%20of%20the%20dryer%20with%20a%20crisp%2C%20freshly%20pressed%20look%20that%20you%20get%20from%20a%20professional%20cleaner%20so%20you'll%20need%20to%20press%20them%20with%20an%20iron%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt-home%20kits%20are%20not%20suitable%20for%20cleaning%20sequined%20or%20heavily%20beaded%20garments%20at%20home%20because%20heat%20from%20the%20dryer%20can%20damage%20the%20decorations.%20Skip%20them%20for%20leather%20or%20suede%20garments%20too.%20These%20have%20special%20cleaning%20requirements%20and%20should%20be%20taken%20to%20a%20professional%20cleaner%20who%20specializes%20in%20leather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20use%20an%20at-home%20kit%20every%20time%20after%20wearing%20a%20garment%2C%20to%20thoroughly%20remove%20stains%20and%20body%20soil%20and%20odors%2C%20you%20should%20take%20your%20clothes%20to%20a%20professional%20cleaner%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20use%20an%20at-home%20dry%20cleaning%20kit%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20leading%20brands%20for%20at-home%20dry%20cleaning%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-41823-20%26h%3D684aef16ceb5f0ee200f2c6e054a64aacbb9203b0db1ded951eb901661eb520c%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42d27%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-dry-clean-clothes-at-home%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fgo.skimresources.com%252F%253Fid%253D35871X943606%2526amp%253Bxs%253D1%2526amp%253Burl%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.target.com%25252Fp%25252Fdryel-at-home-dry-cleaner-starter-kit-4-loads%25252F-%25252FA-14711590%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDryel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and