ent%252Fdp%252FB07F46CBGV%252Fref%253Das_li_ss_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Dll1%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%2526amp%253BlinkId%253Da8461ac42e21251e05d0128a14f7ea9f%2526amp%253Blanguage%253Den_US%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETide%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20contains%20enough%20enzymes%20to%20break%20down%20soil%20and%20sweat%20on%20the%20interior%20surface%20of%20the%20mask.%20When%20hand-washing%2C%20add%20about%20one%20teaspoon%20of%20detergent%20to%20the%20basin%20of%20water%20before%20adding%20the%20masks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUse%20warm%20or%20cool%20water%20to%20rinse%20the%20masks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECloth%20masks%20should%20be%20dried%20on%20the%20highest%20heat%20cycle%20in%20an%20automatic%20dryer.%20If%20you%20do%20not%20have%20a%20dryer%2C%20place%20the%20masks%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%26h%3Da1d704060c08209dba9b97541b3835374f16ea8c922b951a7eb8544e95150f8b%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42d77%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-clean-sanitize-face-mask%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FAmazonBasics-Foldable-Drying-Rack-Chrome%252Fdp%252FB00H7P1G7C%252Fref%253Das_li_ss_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Dll1%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%2526amp%253BlinkId%253Dad8d2a6597f8d742509c9b6ecdcc758a%2526amp%253Blanguage%253Den_US%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrying%20rack%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20direct%20sunlight.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20the%20masks%20are%20dry%2C%20store%20them%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%26h%3D116ef9478c8ded565bc923b9be60728b1fea6ed87f3a17d195edf02140fb29d9%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42d77%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-clean-sanitize-face-mask%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fdp%252FB01F445OLG%252Fref%253Das_li_ss_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Dll1%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%2526amp%253BlinkId%253Dc4280b9d606750e5071c25dabc57e39f%2526amp%253Blanguage%253Den_US%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecovered%20container%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20bag%20until%20you're%20ready%20to%20wear%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20disinfect%20cloth%20masks%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20years%20of%20testing%20different%20cleaning%20methods%20on%20fabrics%20in%20a%20textile%20lab%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20washing%20cotton%20in%20hot%20water%20and%20drying%20it%20on%20the%20high%20heat%20setting%20will%20effectively%20sanitize%20it.%20However%2C%20if%20someone%20in%20your%20household%20is%20ill%20or%20has%20a%20compromised%20immune%20system%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20add%20a%20disinfectant%20to%20the%20wash%20cycle%20when%20cleaning%20fabric%20masks%20to%20ensure%20that%20germs%20are%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20type%20of%20disinfectant%20you%20should%20use%20depends%20on%20your%20mask's%20fabric.%20While%20chlorine%20bleach%20is%20an%20excellent%20disinfectant%2C%20it%20can%20weaken%20and%20discolor%20fabrics%20if%20used%20incorrectly.%20Always%20read%20product%20labels%20and%20carefully%20follow%20directions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20novel%20coronavirus%2C%20some%20of%20these%20products%20might%20be%20currently%20unavailable%20online%20or%20only%20available%20in-store.%20We've%20decided%20to%20keep%20the%20links%20as%20we've%20seen%20availability%20come%20in%20and%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ETypes%20of%20disinfectants%20to%20use%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChlorine%20bleach%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%26h%3D47d0b3b1ecf6a0536d55a988f56d116831d6fbf1799fbe263b5aca60b07613fb%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42d77%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-clean-sanitize-face-mask%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fgoto.target.com%252Fc%252F196318%252F81938%252F2092%253Fu%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.target.com%25252Fp%25252Fclorox-disinfecting-bleach-regular-121oz%25252F-%25252FA-14711215%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClorox%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20disinfectant%20in%20the%20wash%20cycle%20and%20is%20best%20suited%20for%20white%20cotton%20fabrics.%20Check%20the%20label%20to%20determine%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20bleach.%20To%20be%20effective%20as%20a%20disinfectant%2C%20there%20must%20be%20a%205.25%25%20to%206.15%25%20concentration%20of%20sodium%20hypochlorite.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPhenolic%20disinfectants%20like%20Lysol%20Laundry%20Sanitizer%20can%20be%20used%20on%20white%20and%20colored%20fabrics.%20Phenolic%20disinfectants%20are%20usually%20added%20during%20the%20rinse%20cycle.%20This%20is%20currently%20unavailable%20but%20we're%20keeping%20the%20link%20here%20in%20case%20it%20becomes%20available%20when%20you're%20shopping.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPine%20oil%20disinfectants%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_042920_how-to-clean-a-face-mask-20%26h%3D49e653ca529063aeb14534142b41813aef3bdb1c415f82274e9f22d4a885a467%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42d77%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-clean-sanitize-face-mask%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fgo.ski