%20form%20than%20the%20small%20ones%2C%20and%20I%20found%20that%20the%20Magic%20Chef%20actually%20over-delivered%20on%20its%20claim%3A%20both%20sizes%20were%20ready%20to%20use%20in%20under%2010%20minutes.%20The%20noise%20level%20was%20no%20higher%20than%20other%20machines%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20useful%20if%20you're%20bringing%20the%20ice%20maker%20into%20a%20small%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20drainage%20port%20is%20on%20the%20underside%20of%20the%20machine%2C%20so%20it%20requires%20some%20finagling%20to%20open%20it%20and%20place%20a%20vessel%20for%20catching%20the%20excess%20water%20underneath.%20I%20did%20notice%20that%20some%20hair%20and%20dust%20particles%20stuck%20to%20the%20machine%20and%20were%20super%20visible%20on%20the%20white%20exterior.%20The%20Magic%20Chef%20can%20be%20used%20outdoors%2C%20but%20as%20with%20all%20of%20the%20best%20ice%20makers%2C%20the%20manufacturer%20recommends%20that%20you%20leave%20it%20in%20its%20final%20position%20for%20about%20an%20hour%20before%20using%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20nugget%3A%20GE%20Opal%20Nugget%20Ice%20Maker%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20image%20of%20the%20Opal%20Crushed%20Ice%20Maker%20next%20to%20a%20glass%20containing%20the%20nugget%20ice%20made%20from%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6102f294aedf2100190efcbb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%2FInsider%3B%20Rachel%20Mendelson%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDimensions%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2013.43%20x%2017.5%20x%2016.5%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDaily%20production%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2024%20pounds%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWater%20capacity%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%201.5%20quarts%2C%204.5%20with%20side%20water%20tank%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIce%20shape%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nugget%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIce%20sizes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%201%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERuns%20quietly%2C%20one%20water%20tank%20is%20enough%20for%20an%20hour%20of%20ice%20production%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBulky%2C%20takes%20longer%20to%20produce%20enough%20ice%20to%20fill%20a%20glass%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENugget%20ice%20has%20its%20devoted%20fans%2C%20but%20there%20are%20few%20countertop%20nugget%20ice%20makers%20on%20the%20market.%20Unless%20you%20have%20an%20ice%20maker%20built%20into%20your%20refrigerator%2C%20making%20the%20perfect%20mint%20julep%20can%20feel%20impossible.%20Enter%20the%20Opal%20Nugget%20Ice%20Maker%3A%20it's%20a%20portable%20machine%20that%20produces%20one%20pound%20of%20crushed%20ice%20in%20an%20hour.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Opal%20is%20about%20%24200%20more%20than%20our%20other%20picks%2C%20but%20that's%20a%20pretty%20standard%20price%20for%20a%20nugget%20ice%20maker.%20The%20machine%20took%20about%20half%20an%20hour%20to%20produce%20enough%20nugget%20ice%20to%20fill%20a%2012%20ounce%20glass%20from%20top%20to%20bottom.%20This%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20since%20nugget%20ice%20is%20small%20and%20condenses%20in%20glasses.%20After%20running%20the%20machine%20for%20an%20hour%2C%20you'll%20have%20enough%20ice%20for%20two%20or%20three%20full%20glasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ice%20pieces%20are%20frozen%20solid%20and%20evenly%20shaped.%20The%20interface%20is%20simple%20and%20the%20machine%20is%20sleek%3B%20though%20it%20takes%20up%20over%20a%20foot%20of%20counter%20space%2C%20it%20is%20not%20an%20eyesore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20machine's%20bulk%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20a%20side%20water%20tank%2C%20which%20enables%20you%20to%20triple%20the%20Opal's%20water%20capacity%20and%20continuously%20make%20ice%20for%20several%20hours%20in%20a%20row.%20It%20was%20easy%20to%20connect%20with%20a%20clearly%20labeled%20tube%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20machine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20an%20ice%20maker%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpace%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Your%20ice%20maker%20can%20be%20placed%20wherever%20there%20is%20a%20sufficient%20electrical%20outlet%2C%20but%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20they're%20heavy%20and%20typically%20need%20to%20be%20kept%20upright%20and%20level%20before%20use.%20Additionally%2C%20you%20should%20leave%20space%20between%20the%20ice%20maker%20and%20heat%20sources%2C%20like%20stoves%20or%20vents%20%E2%80%94%20the%20higher%20the%20ambient%20temperature%2C%20the%20longer%20ice%20takes%20to%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EType%20of%20ice%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Most%20ice%20makers%20make%20bullet%20ice%2C%20which%20is%20cylindrical%20with%20a%20rounded%20base%20and%20a%20hollow%20middle.%20Bullet%20ice%20starts%20to%20melt%20fairly%20quickly%2C%20and%20even%20the%20best%20ice%20makers%20do%20not%20have%20insulated%20baskets%20for%20long-term%20storage%2C%20so%20if%20you're%20running%20one%20during%20a%20party%2C%20you%20will%20have%20to%20periodically%20empty%20it%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpeed%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20of%20the%20main%20benefits%20of%20an%20ice%20maker%20is%20how%20quickly%20it%20produces%20ice%20compared%20to%20leaving%20a%20tray%20in%20your%20freezer.%20Any%20machine%20that%20makes%20bullet%20ice%20will%20be%20the%20fastest%20way%20to%20fill%20your%20glass%20or%20small%20cooler%2C%20while%20nugget%20or%20cube%20ice%20makers%20add%20ten%20or%20so%20more%20minutes%20to%20the%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20tested%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20glasses%20of%20water%20with%20ice%20from%20two%20of%20the%20ice%20makers%20we%20tested.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61016be10d35a9001825991f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20put%20five%20of%20the%20best%20ice%20makers%20through%20a%20series%20of%20tests%20to%20determine%20which%20ones%20performed%20consistently%20well.%20We%20chose%20ice%20makers%20that%20produced%20between%2026%20and%2028%20pounds%20of%20ice%20daily%2C%20which%20is%20the%20market%20average.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpeed%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Each%20ice%20maker%20we%20tested%20promised%20to%20make%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20cubes%20in%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20so%20we%20tested%20the%20accuracy%20of%20those%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECapacity%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20measured%20the%20water%20reservoir%20capacity%20by%20filling%20it%20with%20a%20quart%20of%20water%20at%20a%20time%20until%20we%20reached%20the%20max%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIce%20quality%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20noted%20if%20the%20ice%20came%20out%20broken%20or%20whole%2C%20and%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20ice%20cubes%20made%20on%20the%20same%20setting%20were%20similar%20in%20shape%20and%20size.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20machine%20had%20multiple%20size%20settings%2C%20we%20evaluated%20the%20sizes%20separately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20compared%20the%20melting%20speeds%20of%20ice%20produced%20by%20the%20best%20ice%20makers%20and%20ice%20from%20traditional%20cube%20trays%20in%20two%20separate%20tests%3A%20one%20where%20the%20ice%20cubes%20were%20placed%20in%20glasses%20of%20water%2C%20and%20one%20where%20the%20ice%20cubes%20were%20left%20out.%20In%20general%2C%20ice%20from%20the%20machines%20melted%20slower%20than%20ice%20from%20the%20traditional%20trays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20use%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20noted%20how%20easy%20it%20was%20to%20lift%20the%20machines%20and%20keep%20them%20level%2C%20as%20well%20as%20how%20much%20effort%20it%20took%20to%20drain%20the%20machines.%20We%20also%20examined%20each%20machine's%20interface%2C%20and%20judged%20them%20on%20simplicity%20and%20intelligibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIce%20maker%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20holding%20three%20semi-clear%20ice%20cubes%20frozen%20together%20from%20the%20Luma%20Comfort%20Clear%20Ice%20Maker%20as%20part%20of%20testing%20for%20the%20best%20ice%20maker.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61016c740d35a90018259948%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20do%20you%20clean%20your%20ice%20maker%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIce%20makers%20have%20specific%20cleaning%20instructions%20in%20their%20manuals%20%E2%80%94%20the%20process%20was%20largely%20the%20same%20for%20the%20five%20machines%20we%20tested.%20Dilute%20detergent%20with%20room%20temperature%20water%20and%20wash%20the%20inside%20of%20the%20water%20tank%20and%20ice%20basket%20with%20a%20soft%20cloth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat%20are%20built-in%20ice%20makers%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20a%20refrigerator's%20ice%20maker%2C%20a%20built-in%20ice%20maker%20is%20directly%20connected%20to%20a%20water%20line%2C%20so%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20fill%20up%20the%20tank%20to%20make%20ice.%20Built-in%20ice%20makers%20are%20insulated%20and%20can%20store%20ice%20up%20to%20half%20the%20daily%20production%20of%20ice%20at%20a%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20drawback%20is%20how%20much%20space%20the%20unit%20takes%20up.%20The%20best%20countertop%20ice%20makers%20can%20be%20tucked%20away%20when%20not%20in%20use%2C%20but%20even%20built-in%20units%20placed%20under%20the%20counter%20are%20bulky%20and%20have%20to%20be%20connected%20to%20a%20water%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EHow%20does%20an%20ice%20maker%20work%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPortable%20ice%20makers%20use%20the%20same%20mechanical%20freezing%20cycle%20as%20refrigerators%20and%20freezers%2C%20just%20on%20a%20smaller%20scale.%20Because%20they're%20not%20connected%20to%20a%20water%20line%2C%20you%20have%20to%20fill%20up%20the%20ice%20maker's%20water%20reservoir%20to%20make%20the%20ice.%20Unlike%20a%20chest%20freezer%2C%20a%20high%20ambient%20temperature%20can%20significantly%20slow%20down%20the%20speed%20of%20a%20portable%20ice%20maker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhy%20does%20bullet%20ice%20melt%20faster%20than%20cubes%20or%20spheres%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMelting%20speed%20is%20determined%20by%20the%20surface%20area%20to%20volume%20ratio.%20Large%20ice%20spheres%20melt%20slower%20than%20traditional%20ice%20cubes%20because%20spheres%20have%20a%20lower%20ratio.%20Bullet%20ice%2C%20with%20its%20hollow%20center%2C%20has%20a%20higher%20ratio%20and%20therefore%20melts%20faster.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20two%20main%20purposes%20of%20ice%20are%20to%20chill%20the%20cocktail%20and%20to%20dilute%20it.%20With%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20you%20build%20a%20cocktail%20and%20how%20you%20like%20to%20enjoy%20it%2C%20ice%20plays%20different%20roles%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ho.%20Fast-melting%20ice%20results%20in%20a%20diluted%20but%20colder%20drink%2C%20while%20slow-melting%20ice%20keeps%20a%20drink%20concentrated%20but%20not%20as%20cold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20read%20more%20about%20when%20and%20why%20to%20use%20different%20ice%20shapes%20and%20sizes%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-ice-cube-tray%23ice-cube-tray-faqs-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-ice-maker%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777263261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F648cb58d51ea980019d6b260%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-ice-maker%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Countertop%20ice%20makers%20are%20quick%20to%20make%20cups%20of%20ice%20and%20great%20for%20parties.%20Here%20are%20the%20best%20ice%20machines%20for%20bullet%20ice%2C%20cubed%20ice%2C%20and%20nugget%20ice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lalig%40businessinsider.com%20(Lily%20Alig)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22OpenAI%20just%20updated%20its%20principles.%20Here's%20what%20changed%20since%20the%20original%20version%2C%206%20years%20ago.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20is%20pictured.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cfc5df6a864f6fcd7bd18c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20shared%20a%20list%20of%20five%20%26quot%3Bprinciples%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20frontier%20model%20lab.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20updated%20its%20guiding%20principles%20in%20a%20major%20way.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%202018%20guidelines%20emphasized%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20far%20more%20than%20the%20latest%20document.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20principles%20imply%20that%20OpenAI%20could%20prioritize%20its%20interests%20over%20universal%20AI%20accessibility.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20just%20shared%20an%20update%20to%20its%20principles%2C%20and%20three%20differences%20stand%20out%20from%20the%202018%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20on%20Sunday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-takes-sam-altman-credibility-to-court-openai-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20a%20list%20of%20five%20%26quot%3Bprinciples%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20frontier%20model%20lab.%20While%20the%20company%20has%20shared%20smaller%20safety%20policy%20shifts%20and%20model%20specs%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20new%20set%20of%20principles%20is%20a%20major%20update%20to%20its%20guidelines%20since%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20was%20founded%20in%20%3Cmark%20data-color%3D%5C%22rgba(0%2C%200%2C%200%2C%200)%5C%22%3EDecember%202015%3C%2Fmark%3E%20as%20a%20nonprofit%20AI%20research%20organization.%20It%20was%20established%20in%20San%20Francisco%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-executive-departures-shake-up-leadership-team-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egroup%20of%20founders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Altman%2C%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20and%20Ilya%20Sutskever%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20left%20after%20disagreements%20over%20its%20transition%20to%20a%20closed-source%2C%20for-profit%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20three%20key%20differences%20between%20the%202018%20and%202026%20documents%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb5a6f2d-3fee-4222-9d03-c33b66aecb21%5C%22%3E1.%20Less%20emphasis%20on%20AGI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202018%20charter%2C%20guidelines%20around%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20highly%20autonomous%20systems%20that%20outperform%20humans%20at%20most%20economically%20valuable%20work%20%E2%80%94%20were%20in%20focus.%20AGI%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20a%20far-fetched%20north%20star%20for%20AI%20labs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202018%20document%2C%20which%20mentioned%20AGI%2012%20times%2C%20read%3A%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20effective%20at%20addressing%20AGI's%20impact%20on%20society%2C%20OpenAI%20must%20be%20on%20the%20cutting%20edge%20of%20AI%20capabilities%E2%80%94policy%20and%20safety%20advocacy%20alone%20would%20be%20insufficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202026%20document%20mentions%20AGI%20twice%2C%20focusing%20on%20AI%20across%20the%20board%20rather%20than%20AGI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20expansion%20of%20our%20long-held%20strategy%20of%20iterative%20deployment%3B%20we%20believe%20society%20needs%20to%20contend%20with%20each%20successive%20level%20of%20AI%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20Sunday's%20blog%20post%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220430b2f1-ef91-44d5-a93e-42a9392e3e16%5C%22%3E2.%20Pivot%20on%20competition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESunday's%20version%20of%20the%20objectives%20is%20a%20180-degree%20shift%20from%20the%20company's%20original%20guidelines%20on%20collaboration%20and%20avoiding%20competition%20with%20rival%20labs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20concerned%20about%20late-stage%20AGI%20development%20becoming%20a%20competitive%20race%20without%20time%20for%20adequate%20safety%20precautions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%202018%20guidelines%20read.%20%26quot%3BTherefore%2C%20if%20a%20value-aligned%2C%20safety-conscious%20project%20comes%20close%20to%20building%20AGI%20before%20we%20do%2C%20we%20commit%20to%20stop%20competing%20with%20and%20start%20assisting%20this%20project.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20document%20skips%20mentions%20of%20sharing%20progress%20and%20stepping%20aside.%20It%20implicitly%20states%20that%20if%20needed%2C%20the%20company%20will%20prioritize%20being%20competitive%20over%20AI%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20also%20acknowledge%20that%20OpenAI%20is%20a%20much%20larger%20force%20in%20the%20world%20than%20it%20was%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20we%20will%20be%20transparent%20about%20when%2C%20how%2C%20and%20why%20our%20operating%20principles%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20concrete%20example%2C%20while%20we%20are%20quite%20confident%20that%20universal%20prosperity%20will%20remain%20really%20important%2C%20we%20can%20imagine%20periods%20in%20the%20future%20where%20we%20have%20to%20trade%20off%20some%20empowerment%20for%20more%20resilience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20OpenAI%20has%20been%20in%20fierce%20competition%20with%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-code-product-chief-users-fomo-anthropic-ai-release-pace-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyounger%20rival%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20h